        <num>CCP 4605</num>
        <heading>4605.  Preference; appointment of notary; discretion of court</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 4605.  Preference; appointment of notary; discretion of court
A partition proceeding shall be tried with preference over other ordinary proceedings.
After the trial of the proceeding, if the court finds that the plaintiff is entitled to a partition of the property, the court shall appoint a notary to make the partition in accordance with law.
Except as otherwise provided in Article 4606, the court has discretion to direct the manner and conditions of effecting the partition, so that it will be most advantageous and convenient to the parties.</p>
        </content>
